<div id="tips">
<h2>Tips</h2>
			<h2>The <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name_with_suffix")> SIM card</h2>
				<p>
					The SIM card is pre-installed. To change the SIM, remove the battery cover and the battery.
				</p>

			<h2>Connected Devices</h2>
			<p>The center card on the <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name_with_suffix")> Home screen shows the number of devices connected to the Primary and Guest networks. Tap this card to see the <strong>Connected Devices</strong> screen then tap a category to see more detailed information on connected or blocked devices.</p>
			<h2>Audio Alerts</h2>
			<p>You can customize your <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name_with_suffix")> audio alerts. From your <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name_with_suffix")> Home screen, tap <strong>Menu</strong> > <strong>Settings</strong> > <strong>Audio Alerts</strong>.</p>
			<h2>Battery Life</h2>
			<p>You can save battery life by adjusting your <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name_with_suffix")> Screen Timeout and Sleep Mode settings. You’ll find them under <strong>Menu</strong> > <strong>Settings</strong>.</p>

			<h2>Wi-Fi Protected Setup (WPS)</h2>
				<p>
					WPS lets you connect devices with a WPS button to your <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name_with_suffix")> Wi-Fi network without entering the password. From the Home screen, go to <strong>Menu</strong> > <strong>Wi-Fi Protected Setup (WPS)</strong> and select the Primary or Guest network and choose <strong>Use WPS Button</strong> or <strong>Enter PIN</strong>. Then follow the onscreen instructions.
				</p>	

			<h2>The Guest Wi-Fi Network</h2>
			<p>
				For added security, share the Guest network to give other’s internet access. Your Guest Wi-Fi network has a separate network name and password from the Primary network and devices on the Guest network can’t access the <tmpl_var _("webui", "webui_product_name_with_suffix")> Admin website.
			</p>

</div>
